# Copy to .env (gitignored, never committed) to configure optional
# remote HTTPS access via Cloudflare Tunnel. Everything works fine
# LAN-only with none of this set.
#
# See docs/remote_access_cloudflare_tunnel.md for full setup steps.

# Note: no API URL configuration is needed. The frontend uses
# same-origin relative paths and nginx proxies /api and /ws to the
# backend, so the same build works on the LAN (offline) and through a
# tunnel. You only need ONE public hostname route in Cloudflare,
# pointing at localhost:8090.

# From Cloudflare Zero Trust dashboard -> Networks -> Tunnels -> your
# tunnel -> "Install and run a connector" step (a long token string).
# Only takes effect when running with: docker compose --profile cloudflare-tunnel up -d
# CLOUDFLARE_TUNNEL_TOKEN=

# Only needed on 32-bit ARM (Raspberry Pi 2/3 on 32-bit Raspberry Pi OS).
# Cloudflare publishes no official armv7 cloudflared image, so an
# unofficial multi-arch build is required there. Leave unset on
# amd64/arm64 to use Cloudflare's own official image.
# CLOUDFLARED_IMAGE=erisamoe/cloudflared:latest

# CCTV camera - USB webcam connected directly to the Pi, relayed via
# go2rtc's native v4l2 support. See docs/cctv_camera_setup.md.
# Only takes effect when running with: docker compose --profile camera up -d
# Defaults to /dev/video0 - override if `ls /dev/video*` on the Pi
# shows your webcam registered at a different path.
# WEBCAM_DEVICE=/dev/video0
